    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know, i'm just really worried about the cost and the wait time at the clinic. it's not a massive gush of blood, it's more like it's just constantly weeping. i've read a lot about medical grade honey being used in hospitals for skin infections and wound healing though... isn't that actually a proven thing? if i just make sure it's super clean, can't i just use that to seal it up and avoid the stitches?",
