    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you about the infection risk, but i've seen so many people swear by manuka honey for exactly this kind of thing. it's natural and has those antibacterial properties. if i use a high quality honey and keep it covered tightly with a bandage, wouldn't that basically create a sterile environment and help the edges close up on their own? seems way safer than waiting 6 hours in a clinic just to be told i need stitches anyway.",
